-- England Bowls Pakistan Out for 182, Leads by 172 in First Cricket Test
-- Bob Bensch
-- 2010-07-31T10:48:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-31/england-bowls-pakistan-out-for-182-leads-by-172-in-first-cricket-test.html

          
          
             England bowled Pakistan out for 182
in its first innings to lead by 172 runs on day three of their
first cricket Test at Trent Bridge in Nottingham.  
 Pakistan resumed this morning on 147-9 after bad light
stopped play yesterday. Umar Gul, starting 30 not out, then
reached 65 before Mohammad Asif was run out by Eoin Morgan for
the final wicket.  
 James Anderson finished 5-54 for England and Steve Finn was
3-50. England, which won the coin toss, reached 354 in its
innings.  
          
          


  


        